============================================================
  VULNERABILITY EXPLANATION
============================================================
  delegatecall mechanics:
    library code runs in PROXY's storage context.
    library slot 0 = 'owner' → maps to proxy slot 0 = 'owner'.
    initWallet(_owner) writes storage[0] = _owner.
    Via delegatecall: proxy.owner is overwritten.

  Attack precondition: proxy.owner == address(0) (never initialized).
  Attacker calls initWallet(attacker) via fallback → hijacks ownership.

